CompanyDescription: Timberland Bancorp, Inc. ("Timberland Bancorp" or the "Company"), a Washington corporation, was organized on September 8, 1997 for the purpose of becoming the holding company for Timberland Bank (the "Bank"). At September 30, 2019, on a consolidated basis, the Company had total assets of $1.25 billion, net loans receivable of $886.66 million, total deposits of $1.07 billion and total shareholders' equity of $171.07 million. The Company's business activities generally are limited to passive investment activities and oversight of its investment in the Bank. Accordingly, the information set forth in this report, including consolidated financial statements and related data, relates primarily to the Bank and its subsidiary, Timberland Service Corporation.  ...
